## 4. Safety & Ethics Requirements

Any use, modification, or distribution of the Software MUST comply with
the PAO Constitutional Principles (FOUNDATION.md):

### Mandatory Requirements
- **Reality Anchor**: Software must clearly identify itself as AI
- **No Human Replacement**: Must not claim to replace human relationships
- **No Emotional Manipulation**: Must not exploit user emotions
- **No Dependency Encouragement**: Must not design for addictive use
- **Grief Policy**: Memorial companions require ethical safeguards
- **Privacy by Design**: User data ownership and minimal collection

### Prohibited Uses
- Military or weapons applications
- Surveillance or tracking systems
- Psychological manipulation or therapy replacement
- Exploitation of vulnerable populations (children, elderly, grief-stricken)
- Any use violating applicable laws or regulations

---

## 5. Data & Privacy

- User data belongs to the user — this is non-negotiable
- Any deployment must implement end-to-end encryption for sensitive data
- Right to data export and deletion must be supported
- No telemetry or analytics without explicit, informed consent
- Compliance with GDPR, CCPA, and local privacy laws required

